A Kaduna State-based pastor, Bawa Madaki has been sentenced to 14 years imprisonment for Child trafficking. The pastor who was arraigned on two counts charges of fraudulently procuring two underage children from their parents was jailed after the court found him guilty of the alleged crime. Delivering the judgment on Monday, Justice Haruna Offor of a High Court in Nasarawa State sentenced Madaki to 14 years’ imprisonment for trafficking two children aged five and seven years old – without an option of fine. Speaking with newsmen after the judgement, Josiah Emerole, Head of Press and Public Relations of the National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP), disclosed that Pastor Madaki’s trial commenced on June 23, 2015, According to him, The accused was arraigned on two counts charges of fraudulently procuring two underage children from their parents. He maintained that the director-general of NAPTIP, Julie Okah Donli has continually cautioned the general public against illegal adoption of underage children and domestic workers. And advice Nigerians who enjoy maltreating and abusing children to desist from doing so. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook